    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS (RECONDITIONING) - OIL PICKUP TUBE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>OIL PICKUP TUBE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the vibration damper removed, remove the oil pickup tube as follows: (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150735">7.35</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .) (Rear sump tube shown).
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the two retaining bolts at the front cover.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Support the oil pickup tube and remove the retaining bolt at the support bracket.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the pickup tube and gasket. Discard the gasket.</para>
                <figure id="ef4150735" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11608" filename="../figcg1/CG11608.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.35. Remove Oil Pickup Tube.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
